{"word":"ὁπόταν","slug":"ὁπόταν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n74625\" key=\"o(po/tan\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὁπότᾰν</orth>, i. e. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁπότ᾽ ἄν,</foreign> as it is freq. written in codd. (the distn. did not exist for the Greeks) : <pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adv.\">Adv.</a></pos>, related to <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅταν</foreign> as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁπότε</foreign> to <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅτε</foreign> (v. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁπότε</foreign>), <sense id=\"n74625.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">whensoever,</tr_> used only with <mood opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"mood\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ subj.\">subj.</a></mood>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:15:209\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">15.209</biblScope></bibl>, etc. (<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl> uses <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁππότε κεν</foreign> in the same way, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:40\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.40</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:229\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">229</biblScope></bibl>, al.): rarely after past tenses, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">πολλὰς . . η̆σθου πλαγάς, ὁπόταν . . νὺξ ὑπολείφθῃ</foreign> (for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁπότε νὺξ ὑπολειφθείη</foreign>) <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg005.perseus-grc1:91\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ El.\">El.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">91</biblScope> </bibl> (anap.): never with ind. in early writers, for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">φθέγξομαι</foreign> (<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:21:340\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">21.340</biblScope> </bibl>), <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἱμείρεται</foreign> (<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:1:41\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.41</biblScope> </bibl>) are <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ep.\">Ep.</a></gram> </gramGrp> <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ aor.\">aor.</a></tns> <mood opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"mood\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ subj.\">subj.</a></mood> forms, and in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:16:282\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">16.282</biblScope> </bibl> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">θῇσιν</foreign> is the right reading : never with opt. save in late writers (unless the Mss. can be trusted in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Alc.\">Alc.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.146a</biblScope> </bibl>), for in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:7:415\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.415</biblScope> </bibl> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁππότ᾽ ἄρ᾽</foreign> is the reading of the best codd. ; in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg007.perseus-grc1:1:3:11\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ X.\">X.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Cyr.\">Cyr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.3.11</biblScope> </bibl> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁπότε ἥκοι</foreign> is the right reading. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n74625.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">as soon as,</tr_> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὁπότ᾽ ἂν τὸ πρῶτον ἴδῃ φάος</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0013.tlg003.perseus-grc1:71\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ h.Ap.\">h.Ap.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">71</biblScope></bibl></cit>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}